{"type":"message","id":"07340512","parentId":"b3f2c818","timestamp":"2026-04-11T03:06:14.216Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"It seems that I don't have access to search using Brave's Search API because I do not have a valid API key stored. In order to proceed with searching for recent AI news, I need to configure my environment or store the required API key.\n\nYou can configure OpenClaw by running the following command in your terminal:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw configure --section web\n```\n\nThis will open an interface where you can set up and manage API keys. Once configured, I should be able to use `web_search` again with the appropriate API key included. Alternatively, you could provide me with a Brave Search API key directly if you have one available.\n\nI'll proceed by using standard web search methods instead of leveraging the API."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"qwen-local:latest","usage":{"input":8190,"output":149,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8339,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775876774210}}
